  <dashboards>
    <dashboard _.fcp.AccessibleZoneTabOrder.true...enable-sort-zone-taborder='true' name='Labor Statistics '>
      <layout-options>
        <title>
          <formatted-text>
            <run>Labor Force Statistics &#10;</run>
            <run fontsize='12'>Total labor force, unemployment as % of labor force and employment in services sector</run>
            <run>Æ </run>
          </formatted-text>
        </title>
      </layout-options>
      <style />
      <size maxheight='800' maxwidth='1000' minheight='800' minwidth='1000' />
      <zones>
        <zone h='100000' id='4' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
          <zone h='98000' id='17' param='vert' type-v2='layout-flow' w='98400' x='800' y='1000'>
            <zone h='9500' id='18' type-v2='title' w='98400' x='800' y='1000'>
              <zone-style>
                <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                <format attr='margin' value='4' />
              </zone-style>
            </zone>
            <zone fixed-size='133' forceUpdate='true' h='17625' id='19' is-fixed='true' type-v2='text' w='98400' x='800' y='10500'>
              <formatted-text>
                <run>The charts on this dashboard presents statistics on the labor force across the regions (2018-2022)  along with figures on the unemployment as percentage of the labor force (2018-2022) both are presented in a time series format and employment in the services sector (2018-2022) which is visualized as a cumulative figure. 

The unemployment chart shows the imapct of COVID-19 where regions like LAC, MENA, and SSA have felt the most impact of COVID on their labor force. SSA ranking in the  unemployment rates have  increased from 5th to 3rd post-COVID indicating the severe damage the pandemic left on SSA&apos;s economies. unemployment rates in the MENA region continues to be the highest across all even after the COVID ended, while on LAC have witnessed a strong recovery in the unemployment rates post pandemic as rates are lower than pre-COVID. When looking at the employment in service sector LAC and ECA have the highest number of employees in the services sector and both regions have seen a quick recovery in unemployment rates post-pandemic, which suggests that the services sector experienced a fast recovery (tourism and hospitality, financial and business services etc..) where jobs were created after the effects of the pandemic softened.  
</run>
              </formatted-text>
              <zone-style>
                <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                <format attr='margin' value='4' />
              </zone-style>
            </zone>
            <zone fixed-size='167' h='21875' id='12' is-fixed='true' name='Labor Force' w='98400' x='800' y='28125'>
              <layout-cache type-h='fixed' type-w='fixed' />
              <zone-style>
                <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                <format attr='margin' value='4' />
