            <zone forceUpdate='true' h='13750' id='16' type-v2='text' w='98400' x='800' y='11500'>
              <formatted-text>
                <run>Charts on this dashboard present the exports of goods and services across the regions as a percentage of GDP (2018-2024), and International tourism receipts as a percentage of exports across the regions (2018-2020) due to data availability. For international tourism receipts, we have removed North America due to its insignificance in the analysis of exports by region. 
MENA, LAC and SSA are the focus regions as they have witnessed the sharpest drop since the onset of COVID-19, and they are ranked as one of the highest globally in terms of international tourism receipts indicating high reliance on the tourism and hospitality sector for employment as well as revenues. This depdences increases their vulnerability to shocks in their economy, as disruptions such as travel restriction, lockdown (stay in home, businesses closed) translate in economic instability. </run>
